<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4889] Different byte to boolean conversion on embedded and client</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4889</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following code prints &quot;true&quot; with the embedded driver and &quot;false&quot; with the client driver:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        PreparedStatement ps = c.prepareStatement(&quot;values cast(? as boolean)&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
        ps.setByte(1, (byte) 32);&lt;br/&gt;
        ResultSet rs = ps.executeQuery();&lt;br/&gt;
        rs.next();&lt;br/&gt;
        System.out.println(rs.getBoolean(1));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If setByte() is replaced with setInt(), they both print &quot;true&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12479281">DERBY-4889</key>
